article.headline: Liberty 55, East Carolina 53
article.story: GREENVILLE, N.C. (AP) -- Alex McLean tipped in a basket at the buzzer Saturday night to lead Liberty past East Carolina 55-53. B.J. Jenkins scored 22 points to lead the Flames (2-3), who led by 13 points midway through the second half before holding on in the final seconds to win it. Gabe Blair scored 15 points to lead the Pirates (1-2). East Carolina rallied to tie it late on a free throw from Brock Young with 18 seconds left. But Liberty got the ball back and McLean tipped in a missed layup from TeeJay Banister to end it.
